# Seven Steps to manage an O' event with Geco

Don't know where to start? Never use a full-featured O software before? Here is a quick guide to manage an orienteering event: seven steps you have to perform to handle a race. Read on for starters.

1\. Use the [Launcher] and the [Stage] panel to set up a new stage.

2\. Load courses from within the [Stage] panel.

3\. Register competitors from the [Runners] panel and using the [Archive].

Boxes 4, 4bis, and 5 illustrates the main loop of events during the stage.

4\. Check E-card configuration in the [Stage] panel and click the Reader button in the [Toolbar].

4bis. Resolve problems directly in the [Runners] panel and using the [Merge] dialog.

5\. Print intermediate [Results].

6\. Don't forget to check the [Stats] to see if everyone is finished

7\. Generate final [Results] for publishing and analysis.

